1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,894
=Episode 7=
(Anniversary)

3
00:01:39,544 --> 00:01:41,024
Ren Xiaoming betrayed our friendship.

4
00:01:41,783 --> 00:01:45,343
She gave the diary we co-wrote
to her husband for publication,

5
00:01:45,943 --> 00:01:46,943
making a lot of money.

6
00:01:48,184 --> 00:01:49,503
Why didn't you confront her?

7
00:01:50,664 --> 00:01:52,143
So I'm asking you to question her.

8
00:01:52,904 --> 00:01:55,863
If she admits the diary
was written by both of us,

9
00:01:56,624 --> 00:01:57,503
make her return it.

10
00:02:00,343 --> 00:02:00,943
Okay.

11
00:02:02,783 --> 00:02:06,143
I... I'll deliver your message.

12
00:02:08,583 --> 00:02:09,384
Li Meng.

13
00:02:10,944 --> 00:02:11,444
What's up?

14
00:02:12,544 --> 00:02:15,183
You could also ask Ren Xiaoming
about Ms. Zhou.

15
00:02:15,944 --> 00:02:19,344
After all, Ms. Zhou was the closest
to both of us back then.

16
00:02:20,023 --> 00:02:21,824
Alright, I'll ask her in person.

17
00:02:30,064 --> 00:02:31,143
I need to talk to you.

18
00:02:31,224 --> 00:02:31,743
Go ahead.

19
00:02:32,623 --> 00:02:36,824
These past few days, I consulted
a top expert in copyright litigation.

20
00:02:40,623 --> 00:02:43,944
So tell me. What are the difficulties?

21
00:02:45,544 --> 00:02:46,984
We lack sufficient evidence.

22
00:02:48,104 --> 00:02:50,143
The chances of winning are slim.

23
00:02:50,944 --> 00:02:52,743
But that doesn't mean
we're out of options.

24
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:56,423
The expert suggested
an indirect approach.

25
00:02:57,143 --> 00:02:58,863
Settle privately
before going to court...

26
00:02:58,863 --> 00:03:01,583
No! I insist on going to court.

27
00:03:02,104 --> 00:03:04,544
I don't want a private settlement.
I want everyone to see.

28
00:03:04,544 --> 00:03:07,423
Wait. What are you being
so stubborn about?

29
00:03:07,423 --> 00:03:09,303
We're going to court
to reclaim the copyrights.

30
00:03:09,303 --> 00:03:10,824
Consider it my obsession, okay?

31
00:03:18,863 --> 00:03:19,743
I'll try my best.

32
00:03:21,423 --> 00:03:25,384
But I just don't understand
who this lawsuit is really for.

33
00:03:28,863 --> 00:03:29,583
(Sorry.)

34
00:03:31,224 --> 00:03:33,023
(I have my reasons for doing this.)

35
00:03:37,264 --> 00:03:37,944
I'm leaving.

36
00:03:46,824 --> 00:03:49,544
Ren Xiaoming, come here.

37
00:03:50,863 --> 00:03:53,104
Listen. Before going to court,
you must keep quiet.

38
00:03:54,344 --> 00:03:56,863
Don't let Liu Xiaoran's backers
find out.

39
00:03:57,743 --> 00:04:00,143
They'll gang up against you.

40
00:04:33,144 --> 00:04:35,664
(Bai Shu, I'll handle everything.)

41
00:04:36,704 --> 00:04:37,743
(Please trust me.)

42
00:04:59,128 --> 00:05:01,592
(Unread message from Liu Xiaoran)

43
00:05:35,544 --> 00:05:36,303
Password correct.

44
00:06:18,784 --> 00:06:20,943
- Happy tenth anniversary!
- Happy tenth anniversary!

45
00:06:53,423 --> 00:06:56,664
Xiaoming, you paid the fee?
The company should reimburse it.

46
00:06:57,344 --> 00:06:59,623
I hit him, so I should pay.

47
00:06:59,664 --> 00:07:00,503
How is he?

48
00:07:00,704 --> 00:07:02,984
Don't worry.
He's been moved to a VIP room.

49
00:07:03,303 --> 00:07:05,584
Nothing too serious. Just a broken nose.

50
00:07:07,104 --> 00:07:09,144
Xiaoming, you're amazing.

51
00:07:09,263 --> 00:07:11,344
You made it trending instantly.

52
00:07:12,263 --> 00:07:15,863
With this exposure,
worth it even if he broke a rib.

53
00:07:16,383 --> 00:07:16,883
Look.

54
00:07:17,863 --> 00:07:19,144
(Ren Xiaoming attacked her husband)
It's been at the top.

55
00:07:20,183 --> 00:07:21,183
For hours.

56
00:07:21,383 --> 00:07:22,263
Oh, my!

57
00:07:22,263 --> 00:07:22,863
Still climbing.

58
00:07:22,863 --> 00:07:24,104
Still rising.

59
00:07:24,183 --> 00:07:25,063
It keeps going up.

60
00:07:25,063 --> 00:07:26,104
You did this?

61
00:07:27,144 --> 00:07:29,423
Imagine the traffic
if the hearing's on the 15th.

62
00:07:30,344 --> 00:07:31,984
Hearing? What hearing?

63
00:07:32,183 --> 00:07:33,303
He didn't tell you?

64
00:07:34,664 --> 00:07:35,383
No.

65
00:07:35,823 --> 00:07:38,743
He plagiarized my work for Breathe.
I'm suing him for copyright.

66
00:07:38,863 --> 00:07:39,743
Plagiarized?

67
00:07:49,863 --> 00:07:51,943
Is Liu Xiaoran okay? His face messed up?

68
00:07:53,423 --> 00:07:54,943
How could you be so brutal?

69
00:07:55,104 --> 00:07:57,704
What? You know it too?

70
00:07:58,423 --> 00:07:59,784
Guess that trending spot paid off.

71
00:08:00,144 --> 00:08:02,423
As soon as I opened Comma,
the video popped up.

72
00:08:02,704 --> 00:08:05,544
You're a meme now. I'll send it to you.

73
00:08:05,544 --> 00:08:06,456
(Ren Xiaoming)

74
00:08:10,024 --> 00:08:11,104
See?

75
00:08:13,623 --> 00:08:16,344
You look like a rabid bear.

76
00:08:19,344 --> 00:08:21,943
How dare you hang up on me?
Feeling brave again?

77
00:08:22,823 --> 00:08:24,803
Daring to hang up on me? Call!

78
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:26,840
(Mom)

79
00:08:30,263 --> 00:08:31,104
I'll call again.

80
00:08:32,503 --> 00:08:34,104
I'll call until your phone dies. Call!

81
00:08:34,104 --> 00:08:35,007
(Ren Xiaoming)

82
00:08:36,472 --> 00:08:37,565
(Mom)

83
00:08:41,824 --> 00:08:44,824
Turned off? Daring to hang up on me.

84
00:08:45,743 --> 00:08:46,543
Who is it?

85
00:08:57,224 --> 00:08:57,824
Who's there?

86
00:09:04,743 --> 00:09:05,424
You old fool!

87
00:09:05,424 --> 00:09:07,184
Stop it! Stop! It's me!

88
00:09:07,743 --> 00:09:09,783
Let me explain! Stop it! Don't!

89
00:09:10,464 --> 00:09:12,903
Who let you in? Who said
you could enter my home?

90
00:09:13,064 --> 00:09:13,863
Just hear me out!

91
00:09:13,984 --> 00:09:16,743
Get out! Get out!

92
00:09:19,944 --> 00:09:20,663
Get out!

93
00:09:25,584 --> 00:09:26,824
Why so rough?

94
00:09:28,863 --> 00:09:30,104
I came to explain.

95
00:09:30,383 --> 00:09:31,064
Explain my foot!

96
00:09:31,304 --> 00:09:33,584
That's my ex-wife. We divorced ages ago.

97
00:09:34,663 --> 00:09:36,383
Divorced but not moving out? How trendy!

98
00:09:37,543 --> 00:09:39,863
You're playing both sides.
That's bigamy!

99
00:09:40,424 --> 00:09:41,944
Try me. I'll drag you to the police.

100
00:09:41,944 --> 00:09:43,383
Then just drag me!

101
00:09:43,543 --> 00:09:44,863
Fine! I'll drag!

102
00:09:44,863 --> 00:09:45,464
Wait...

103
00:09:46,824 --> 00:09:49,743
I drag you here first. Now, sit down.

104
00:09:52,743 --> 00:09:54,503
Drag me to the police.
See what they say.

105
00:09:55,023 --> 00:09:56,064
What they say?

106
00:09:57,944 --> 00:09:58,984
Explain it to me first.

107
00:10:00,944 --> 00:10:01,863
Meili.

108
00:10:02,263 --> 00:10:02,944
Meili?

109
00:10:04,503 --> 00:10:06,383
No, Wu Meili.

110
00:10:07,304 --> 00:10:10,623
We divorced 15 years ago.

111
00:10:13,104 --> 00:10:13,944
Why?

112
00:10:18,263 --> 00:10:19,623
She thought I was useless.

113
00:10:21,304 --> 00:10:22,824
Said life with me was boring.

114
00:10:25,064 --> 00:10:30,464
She also said being with me was like
threading a needle, just seeing the end.

115
00:10:31,543 --> 00:10:33,424
So I thought, "Fine. Let's divorce."

116
00:10:37,304 --> 00:10:38,263
But then,

117
00:10:39,944 --> 00:10:40,944
just half a year later,

118
00:10:41,184 --> 00:10:42,263
she found a new partner.

119
00:10:42,903 --> 00:10:44,944
Off she went to Spain.

120
00:10:45,743 --> 00:10:48,104
Spain? For bullfighting?

121
00:10:49,863 --> 00:10:52,064
So you got dumped, huh?

122
00:10:53,184 --> 00:10:54,374
Dumped...

123
00:10:55,288 --> 00:10:56,344
So what if she dumped me?

124
00:10:58,623 --> 00:11:00,704
Around fall... Yes.

125
00:11:01,344 --> 00:11:04,184
Just when we were talking
about getting married.

126
00:11:04,863 --> 00:11:07,143
Who knows why she came back.

127
00:11:09,984 --> 00:11:13,064
I thought she's the mother
of our two sons.

128
00:11:14,184 --> 00:11:17,783
She had nowhere to live,
so I let her stay temporarily.

129
00:11:22,064 --> 00:11:26,503
At first, she just
left her stuff everywhere.

130
00:11:27,344 --> 00:11:30,503
Then, you know,
the kids started accepting her.

131
00:11:32,304 --> 00:11:35,224
She naturally became part of the family.

132
00:11:38,064 --> 00:11:40,863
Later, my sons talked to me.

133
00:11:41,783 --> 00:11:44,543
They said, "Dad, you're both so old now.

134
00:11:44,543 --> 00:11:47,064
Stop fussing and just
live together properly."

135
00:11:49,464 --> 00:11:52,464
Suddenly, I was like the one
abandoning the family.

136
00:11:54,023 --> 00:11:54,824
What mess is this?

137
00:11:55,584 --> 00:11:59,503
Fine. Let's divorce.
You go back and live happily with her.

138
00:12:00,424 --> 00:12:03,783
Shame about the gift money.
I have to return them all.

139
00:12:04,023 --> 00:12:06,184
Or people might think
I was scamming with a wedding.

140
00:12:14,383 --> 00:12:16,344
Meiyan, why aren't you
kicking up a fuss?

141
00:12:17,503 --> 00:12:18,184
Over what?

142
00:12:19,464 --> 00:12:21,304
Cause a ruckus
over an old codger like you?

143
00:12:22,224 --> 00:12:24,344
Old... Old codger? Me?

144
00:12:25,944 --> 00:12:26,543
It's hilarious.

145
00:12:29,344 --> 00:12:30,543
What are you showing off?

146
00:12:31,023 --> 00:12:33,263
If I were younger,
I'd take both of you down!

147
00:12:33,944 --> 00:12:35,104
What kind of man are you?

148
00:12:35,863 --> 00:12:37,824
Making us two women unsure
who's the other woman!

149
00:12:37,984 --> 00:12:38,584
Disgusting!

150
00:12:43,543 --> 00:12:44,104
What?

151
00:12:45,944 --> 00:12:47,304
I want to live properly with you.

152
00:12:47,543 --> 00:12:48,543
I don't.

153
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:52,824
Meiyan,

154
00:12:55,263 --> 00:12:58,184
I want to spend

155
00:12:59,424 --> 00:13:00,663
the rest of my life with you.

156
00:13:01,344 --> 00:13:03,623
The past is behind us.

157
00:13:04,944 --> 00:13:07,143
We are the start of a beautiful future.

158
00:13:10,064 --> 00:13:11,224
Nice poem.

159
00:13:13,824 --> 00:13:16,743
Then why are you still tangled
with the past?

160
00:13:19,704 --> 00:13:21,143
Who's tangled?

161
00:13:22,824 --> 00:13:25,383
Who's tangled? Who?

162
00:13:26,944 --> 00:13:29,383
Who's tangled? Look who's tangled!

163
00:13:52,464 --> 00:13:55,104
Drinking cold drinks so early
hurts your yang energy.

164
00:14:01,064 --> 00:14:02,464
Shouldn't you be in the hospital?

165
00:14:02,824 --> 00:14:05,104
Shouldn't you be
in the hospital with me?

166
00:14:06,824 --> 00:14:08,104
Chen Junhang isn't with you?

167
00:14:09,383 --> 00:14:10,863
Taken away by the police.

168
00:14:12,263 --> 00:14:12,783
Why?

169
00:14:13,424 --> 00:14:14,064
Assault.

170
00:14:14,623 --> 00:14:15,143
Assault who?

171
00:14:15,424 --> 00:14:16,263
Me.

172
00:14:16,743 --> 00:14:17,623
Liu Xiaoran.

173
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:20,584
Wake up.

174
00:14:21,704 --> 00:14:23,824
Why didn't you tell me
the book was plagiarized?

175
00:14:24,623 --> 00:14:27,863
If Ren Xiaoming didn't mention
the hearing, I'd still be in the dark.

176
00:14:28,984 --> 00:14:30,304
Listen to me.

177
00:14:30,344 --> 00:14:31,304
Don't say a word.

178
00:14:31,344 --> 00:14:33,704
I'll tell the platform, publisher,
and our major investor.

179
00:14:33,984 --> 00:14:36,143
I won't take the fall
for what you've done.

180
00:14:37,184 --> 00:14:38,263
Don't drag me down.

181
00:14:40,924 --> 00:14:41,424
What?

182
00:14:41,424 --> 00:14:44,863
Don't. I'll tell you a huge secret.

183
00:14:45,304 --> 00:14:46,263
What huge secret?

184
00:14:46,944 --> 00:14:47,444
Come on.

185
00:14:54,383 --> 00:14:57,344
Let go! What are you doing?
Liu Xiaoran...

186
00:14:57,383 --> 00:14:58,104
Assault!

187
00:14:58,104 --> 00:14:59,304
Trying to set me up?

188
00:15:02,104 --> 00:15:03,464
Chen Junhang hits people?

189
00:15:07,143 --> 00:15:08,824
If you knew Chen Junhang would hit me,

190
00:15:09,104 --> 00:15:11,143
would you still have told him
about the hearing?

191
00:15:11,743 --> 00:15:14,263
He has the right to know.
He's your partner.

192
00:15:15,383 --> 00:15:16,944
Investor, to be precise.

193
00:15:18,344 --> 00:15:19,663
You're an idiot.

194
00:15:21,023 --> 00:15:22,743
You know he's my investor.

195
00:15:22,944 --> 00:15:24,984
So why tell him
about the hearing in advance?

196
00:15:25,944 --> 00:15:28,704
You thought he'd help
settle out of court?

197
00:15:29,344 --> 00:15:32,584
No. He's a profit-driven businessman.

198
00:15:32,824 --> 00:15:35,663
He'll sacrifice the pawn
to save the king, and I'm the pawn.

199
00:15:36,023 --> 00:15:39,623
If I get in trouble,
he won't share the risk.

200
00:15:39,743 --> 00:15:42,263
He'll distance himself with the others,

201
00:15:42,263 --> 00:15:43,543
cutting off all my retreats.

202
00:15:43,543 --> 00:15:46,944
I never planned to settle.
I will fight this lawsuit.

203
00:15:47,663 --> 00:15:49,912
You didn't tell him, because you thought
there was hope.

204
00:15:50,743 --> 00:15:54,104
You'd try every way to get me to drop
the lawsuit until the very last moment.

205
00:15:55,944 --> 00:15:57,023
So he must know.

206
00:15:57,984 --> 00:15:59,383
I want to crush any hope you have.

207
00:16:01,064 --> 00:16:03,623
I'm helping you face reality.

208
00:16:04,824 --> 00:16:07,304
Nonsense! You're just trying to ruin me.

209
00:16:07,783 --> 00:16:08,824
You want to destroy me.

210
00:16:10,584 --> 00:16:12,503
Was this on purpose? Was it?

211
00:16:12,503 --> 00:16:13,944
How many messages did I send you?

212
00:16:14,383 --> 00:16:17,143
I wanted to tell you about the party.
How could you not see them?

213
00:16:17,143 --> 00:16:19,143
If I had seen them,
I wouldn't have come back.

214
00:16:19,543 --> 00:16:21,464
How could I exploit
my wedding anniversary?

215
00:16:21,623 --> 00:16:22,863
You did it on purpose.

216
00:16:22,944 --> 00:16:24,543
Liu Xiaoran, keep your mind clean!

217
00:16:25,344 --> 00:16:26,344
You're lecturing me?

218
00:16:27,424 --> 00:16:30,143
I just haven't said anything.
Don't think I know nothing.

219
00:16:30,543 --> 00:16:33,143
You send money to that guy
every month via WeChat.

220
00:16:33,623 --> 00:16:36,143
Right? What is he? First love?

221
00:16:37,304 --> 00:16:38,224
You checked my WeChat?

222
00:16:40,344 --> 00:16:42,944
I checked your WeChat.
I also opened your packages.

223
00:16:43,383 --> 00:16:45,023
I even installed cameras, watching you!

224
00:16:45,104 --> 00:16:45,663
So what?

225
00:16:46,224 --> 00:16:48,424
Because you're shameless!
You're keeping a lover!

226
00:16:49,064 --> 00:16:52,503
You send him at least 5,000 yuan
every month. For what?

227
00:16:53,104 --> 00:16:54,503
What services does he provide?

228
00:16:59,704 --> 00:17:03,944
20040601, this is
your real anniversary, isn't it?

229
00:17:05,224 --> 00:17:07,063
All your passwords are this date.

230
00:17:08,424 --> 00:17:10,944
What day was it?
The day you lost your virginity?

231
00:17:12,263 --> 00:17:14,704
That's right! It's my anniversary!

232
00:17:17,184 --> 00:17:18,624
I'll never forget it.

233
00:17:26,503 --> 00:17:27,144
Abuser...

234
00:17:28,583 --> 00:17:29,303
Domestic violence.

235
00:17:30,296 --> 00:17:32,783
(Qidaohezi, 2004)

236
00:17:32,783 --> 00:17:35,224
(I don't know if all happy marriages
are the same.)

237
00:17:36,303 --> 00:17:39,704
(But unhappy marriages
truly come in many forms.)

238
00:17:46,984 --> 00:17:47,823
You'll be home soon.

239
00:17:51,984 --> 00:17:53,263
I won't be able to sleep again.

240
00:18:01,864 --> 00:18:04,624
Then I'll pick you up
for the carnival tomorrow morning.

241
00:18:05,303 --> 00:18:05,864
Wait for me.

242
00:18:10,063 --> 00:18:11,023
Did it hurt?

243
00:18:11,184 --> 00:18:11,944
It's fine.

244
00:18:14,743 --> 00:18:16,343
Take care. See you tomorrow.

245
00:18:16,343 --> 00:18:18,023
Absolutely. Miss me.

246
00:18:18,184 --> 00:18:18,684
Okay.

247
00:18:30,063 --> 00:18:30,783
Meiyan.

248
00:18:37,103 --> 00:18:38,023
Remember to miss me.

249
00:18:45,263 --> 00:18:49,303
♪Summer blooms on the branches♪

250
00:18:49,384 --> 00:18:52,984
♪Roses, roses, I love you♪

251
00:18:57,263 --> 00:18:58,144
Whose car is that?

252
00:19:00,503 --> 00:19:03,303
You saw it? Mr. Sun's.

253
00:19:03,664 --> 00:19:05,263
The one you spat on.

254
00:19:05,944 --> 00:19:09,184
Your head is really hard.
Didn't hurt his car, did you?

255
00:19:12,424 --> 00:19:13,624
Tomorrow is Children's Day.

256
00:19:13,704 --> 00:19:17,384
Mr. Sun said he'll take us
to the carnival in La City at night.

257
00:19:18,263 --> 00:19:19,103
Awesome!

258
00:19:19,543 --> 00:19:21,184
Xiaofei, we're going to the carnival!

259
00:19:21,583 --> 00:19:23,303
I'm not going. I need to study.

260
00:19:24,103 --> 00:19:25,424
Well then, you study hard.

261
00:19:28,384 --> 00:19:29,063
Wait a minute.

262
00:19:30,624 --> 00:19:31,624
I changed my mind.

263
00:19:32,144 --> 00:19:34,583
Sharpening the axe doesn't
delay the chopping. I'm going too.

264
00:19:34,823 --> 00:19:38,664
Forget about it.
Mr. Sun's car doesn't have enough room.

265
00:19:38,984 --> 00:19:40,664
- The Benz can't fit four people?
- The Benz can't fit four people?

266
00:19:41,303 --> 00:19:43,800
Mr. Sun has a daughter.

267
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,184
- Five people can fit too.
- Five people can fit too.

268
00:19:45,224 --> 00:19:47,624
I don't mind being squeezed.
I'm going. I'll take the Benz.

269
00:19:47,664 --> 00:19:48,424
Same here.

270
00:19:49,944 --> 00:19:53,944
The night tickets for the carnival
are hard to get. He only got four.

271
00:19:55,743 --> 00:19:59,224
So when you said "we" just now,
you meant you and Ren Xiaofei all along?

272
00:20:00,543 --> 00:20:03,664
Well then, "we" go. I won't go.

273
00:20:10,543 --> 00:20:13,864
I will make you some dumplings tomorrow.
Cook them yourself when you get back.

274
00:20:15,944 --> 00:20:17,424
I don't need them. I don't want them.

275
00:20:25,263 --> 00:20:26,743
Let's get out of here.

276
00:20:53,783 --> 00:20:54,944
(It's a gloomy night.)

277
00:20:55,464 --> 00:20:59,103
(Because I remembered something,
it became less frustrating.)

278
00:21:07,583 --> 00:21:10,624
(20040601 is Bai Shu's birthday.)

279
00:21:11,704 --> 00:21:13,704
(I want to give her a gift myself.)

280
00:21:15,063 --> 00:21:16,224
Happy birthday.

281
00:21:33,656 --> 00:21:36,600
(Qidian Middle School)

282
00:21:50,103 --> 00:21:51,503
Happy birthday!

283
00:21:53,240 --> 00:21:54,104
(Happy Birthday)

284
00:21:54,944 --> 00:21:58,063
Xiaoming, I'm sorry.
I don't like celebrating birthdays.

285
00:21:59,503 --> 00:22:01,503
It's fine.
I don't celebrate mine either.

286
00:22:02,263 --> 00:22:04,864
Not because I dislike it.
There's just no one to celebrate with.

287
00:22:09,103 --> 00:22:09,823
This is for you.

288
00:22:28,023 --> 00:22:29,343
Is it that scary?

289
00:22:30,343 --> 00:22:34,303
It is the IV tubing my mom brought back
from the hospital. I wove it myself.

290
00:22:37,464 --> 00:22:38,224
Thank you.

291
00:22:39,743 --> 00:22:40,664
You don't like it?

292
00:22:41,303 --> 00:22:42,103
I like it.

293
00:22:42,944 --> 00:22:45,343
You're lying.
If you don't like it, just say so.

294
00:22:45,664 --> 00:22:47,823
I can weave a little rabbit with it.
Do you like that?

295
00:22:48,184 --> 00:22:49,144
I like rabbits.

296
00:22:49,743 --> 00:22:50,944
Then I'll weave one next time.

297
00:22:51,063 --> 00:22:51,743
Okay.

298
00:22:53,063 --> 00:22:53,743
Xiaoming.

299
00:22:55,583 --> 00:22:57,343
I can't go home with you
after school today.

300
00:22:59,823 --> 00:23:00,743
She's picking you up?

301
00:23:02,384 --> 00:23:03,743
She's sending a driver.

302
00:23:04,144 --> 00:23:07,063
Your mom has a driver?
That's quite the luxury.

303
00:23:09,944 --> 00:23:12,343
However bad she is, at least
she celebrates your birthday.

304
00:23:13,664 --> 00:23:14,944
It's not as good as you imagine.

305
00:23:19,424 --> 00:23:20,424
Please accept this.

306
00:23:23,783 --> 00:23:24,503
You made this?

307
00:23:26,503 --> 00:23:27,103
It's wonderful.

308
00:23:30,263 --> 00:23:31,464
Keep it for me.

309
00:23:32,864 --> 00:23:35,503
I'll come to your place tonight.
Wait for me.

310
00:23:36,464 --> 00:23:40,263
No need to comfort me.
I've gotten used to it since childhood.

311
00:23:41,144 --> 00:23:42,624
Just enjoy your birthday at home.

312
00:23:42,984 --> 00:23:45,384
If I say I'm coming, I will.
Wait for me.

313
00:23:46,144 --> 00:23:48,944
Suit yourself then. Anyway,
my mom and Xiaofei won't be home.

314
00:23:50,464 --> 00:23:51,343
Xiaoming.

315
00:23:56,144 --> 00:23:57,263
You should

316
00:23:58,503 --> 00:23:59,743
keep this pen today.

317
00:24:02,543 --> 00:24:03,543
See you tonight.

318
00:24:05,144 --> 00:24:08,103
Wait for me. See you tonight.

319
00:24:51,384 --> 00:24:52,583
Happy birthday.

320
00:25:00,743 --> 00:25:01,263
Come.

321
00:25:04,384 --> 00:25:05,263
Go wash your hands.

322
00:25:06,303 --> 00:25:08,503
I prepared all your favorite foods.

323
00:25:09,583 --> 00:25:10,664
It's your birthday.

324
00:25:15,984 --> 00:25:17,384
Today isn't my birthday.

325
00:25:21,023 --> 00:25:22,103
I'm not dead.

326
00:25:23,464 --> 00:25:24,440
I don't eat offerings.

327
00:25:25,503 --> 00:25:27,063
You want a repeat of last year?

328
00:25:36,503 --> 00:25:39,464
Be good. Can you just behave

329
00:25:40,944 --> 00:25:42,783
and get through this year's birthday?

330
00:25:47,343 --> 00:25:51,063
That 12-year-old Bai Shu died

331
00:25:53,343 --> 00:25:54,583
on this very day 15 years ago.

332
00:27:09,336 --> 00:27:11,640
(Happy Birthday, Bai Shu)

333
00:27:13,144 --> 00:27:16,424
♪Happy birthday to you♪

334
00:27:17,343 --> 00:27:21,224
♪Happy birthday to you♪

335
00:27:21,743 --> 00:27:26,384
♪Happy birthday to you♪

336
00:27:26,864 --> 00:27:31,144
♪Happy birthday to you♪

337
00:27:32,384 --> 00:27:35,944
Happy birthday to my daughter.

338
00:29:44,023 --> 00:29:44,823
I'll bag it for you.

339
00:29:44,944 --> 00:29:45,583
Okay.

340
00:29:46,503 --> 00:29:47,704
- If you like it, come back for more.
- I'm leaving.

341
00:29:47,704 --> 00:29:48,204
Thanks.

342
00:29:48,944 --> 00:29:50,303
Honey, money.

343
00:29:50,303 --> 00:29:51,184
What are you doing?

344
00:29:53,063 --> 00:29:55,944
Yuqiong, my good boy.
This isn't your concern.

345
00:29:56,864 --> 00:29:58,783
I've had too much to drink.
Get me some water.

346
00:29:59,343 --> 00:30:00,023
Get it yourself.

347
00:30:00,103 --> 00:30:00,783
Good boy.

348
00:30:01,864 --> 00:30:03,864
I'll definitely
turn things around this time.

349
00:30:04,184 --> 00:30:07,743
Soon, we won't have to live
like this anymore.

350
00:30:07,743 --> 00:30:08,904
Turn what around?

351
00:30:09,503 --> 00:30:10,103
Good boy.

352
00:30:13,664 --> 00:30:14,743
Trying to scald me?

353
00:30:16,343 --> 00:30:17,464
I want money.

354
00:30:17,543 --> 00:30:18,063
You...

355
00:30:18,224 --> 00:30:18,864
Go.

356
00:30:19,103 --> 00:30:20,424
- Give me the money!
- I don't have it!

357
00:30:20,424 --> 00:30:21,144
I want money!

358
00:30:21,144 --> 00:30:21,743
Don't have it!

359
00:30:21,743 --> 00:30:22,464
Move! Get lost!

360
00:30:22,503 --> 00:30:23,843
Yuqiong!

361
00:30:23,984 --> 00:30:25,144
Money! Give me the money!

362
00:30:25,144 --> 00:30:26,303
- Let go!
- Give me the money!

363
00:30:26,543 --> 00:30:27,343
What are you doing?

364
00:30:27,343 --> 00:30:29,023
The money! Give me the money!

365
00:30:29,023 --> 00:30:30,303
No! Stop it!

366
00:30:57,103 --> 00:30:59,864
Girl! Who are you?
Where did you even come from?

367
00:31:01,063 --> 00:31:03,224
You dare hit me? I'll kill you!

368
00:31:05,624 --> 00:31:06,224
Yuqiong!

369
00:31:07,303 --> 00:31:07,984
He Yuqiong!

370
00:31:08,144 --> 00:31:09,704
Here! Take it!

371
00:31:10,103 --> 00:31:11,563
This is all I made today. Go.

372
00:31:11,624 --> 00:31:13,384
You should've just taken it out earlier.

373
00:31:13,384 --> 00:31:14,343
Don't give it to him!

374
00:31:16,864 --> 00:31:17,783
I'll get some tissue.

375
00:31:20,103 --> 00:31:20,823
Are you okay?

376
00:31:21,263 --> 00:31:22,624
Yuqiong, let me see.

377
00:31:26,783 --> 00:31:27,624
Where are you going?

378
00:31:28,063 --> 00:31:29,103
I'll call the police.

379
00:31:29,984 --> 00:31:30,583
Don't.

380
00:31:30,984 --> 00:31:33,464
He hit you and stole money!

381
00:31:33,783 --> 00:31:34,583
He's my dad.

382
00:31:47,984 --> 00:31:49,823
Does your dad often hit you like this?

383
00:31:50,384 --> 00:31:53,944
Not really. He just loses his mind
after drinking.

384
00:31:54,503 --> 00:31:55,783
That's still unacceptable.

385
00:31:56,343 --> 00:31:58,543
If he does this again, call the police.

386
00:31:58,543 --> 00:31:59,503
Let them deal with him.

387
00:32:02,184 --> 00:32:05,823
Domestic violence is despicable.
I would never become like him.

388
00:32:09,224 --> 00:32:11,944
I was going to tell you
how miserable I am.

389
00:32:12,823 --> 00:32:15,184
But compared to you,
I guess I'm doing okay.

390
00:32:16,263 --> 00:32:17,303
So who bullied you?

391
00:32:19,664 --> 00:32:22,263
My mom took my brother
to La City to see fireworks.

392
00:32:23,464 --> 00:32:24,303
They didn't take you?

393
00:32:25,224 --> 00:32:26,944
If they had, would I be here?

394
00:32:28,063 --> 00:32:28,864
That's your misery?

395
00:32:31,503 --> 00:32:34,023
I forgot my keys, so I can't get in.

396
00:32:34,783 --> 00:32:36,224
I haven't eaten a thing all day.

397
00:32:38,144 --> 00:32:39,144
Wait here.

398
00:32:54,823 --> 00:32:58,783
Xiaoming. Ren Xiaoming? Xiaoming.

399
00:32:59,464 --> 00:33:02,783
Didn't we agree you'd wait at home?
Where did you go?

400
00:33:04,704 --> 00:33:05,343
How is it?

401
00:33:07,263 --> 00:33:08,504
I can actually see them here.

402
00:33:10,023 --> 00:33:11,063
They just look so small.

403
00:33:12,023 --> 00:33:14,184
Don't be ungrateful.
At least you can see them.

404
00:33:20,543 --> 00:33:24,704
Look, there's the moon.
It's huge, so round and big.

405
00:33:27,583 --> 00:33:29,103
There are so many stars over there.

406
00:33:31,384 --> 00:33:32,503
That's Altair.

407
00:33:33,503 --> 00:33:35,624
Those three stars in a row
are his carrying pole.

408
00:33:36,263 --> 00:33:38,343
Ever heard of Orion shooting Sirius?

409
00:33:39,023 --> 00:33:42,263
Sirius is the brightest star
we can see at night.

410
00:33:42,783 --> 00:33:44,984
But we can't see it now.
It has to be winter.

411
00:33:46,424 --> 00:33:47,664
You even know this stuff?

412
00:33:52,263 --> 00:33:52,944
He taught me.

413
00:33:54,783 --> 00:33:55,543
Who?

414
00:34:04,743 --> 00:34:07,664
He and my mom used to be workers
at the optical instruments factory.

415
00:34:08,824 --> 00:34:12,223
The optical instruments factory?
Didn't that shut down years ago?

416
00:34:14,623 --> 00:34:18,063
Before it closed, they both worked
in the polishing workshop.

417
00:34:18,944 --> 00:34:19,984
Let me show you.

418
00:34:25,103 --> 00:34:26,703
They polished the lenses on this.

419
00:34:29,304 --> 00:34:30,063
It's yours?

420
00:34:31,663 --> 00:34:32,264
His.

421
00:34:36,703 --> 00:34:40,703
Alright. The lenses are fine. With luck,
you can see the craters on the moon.

422
00:34:44,264 --> 00:34:45,424
I see the little rabbit.

423
00:34:46,143 --> 00:34:46,984
Really?

424
00:34:52,984 --> 00:34:54,063
Seriously?

425
00:34:55,103 --> 00:34:56,344
You actually believed me?

426
00:35:00,503 --> 00:35:01,904
What else can I see?

427
00:35:04,103 --> 00:35:07,583
For others, you need a professional
telescope. This one can't see them.

428
00:35:08,464 --> 00:35:10,543
Those professional telescopes
are crazy expensive.

429
00:35:12,744 --> 00:35:13,503
How expensive?

430
00:35:14,103 --> 00:35:16,384
Maybe tens of thousands?
I don't know, never seen one.

431
00:35:17,103 --> 00:35:19,264
Wait until I make big money,
I'll get you one.

432
00:35:19,744 --> 00:35:22,264
Thanks! You said it.
Don't go back on your word.

433
00:35:24,103 --> 00:35:26,424
What do you want?
I'll get you something too.

434
00:35:28,744 --> 00:35:30,984
Me? I want a star.

435
00:35:34,384 --> 00:35:35,984
That's easy.

436
00:35:37,223 --> 00:35:40,223
Quit bragging! You can get me a star?

437
00:35:40,223 --> 00:35:41,384
Why don't you just fly?

438
00:35:44,143 --> 00:35:45,304
I'll give you my name.

439
00:35:46,464 --> 00:35:48,583
Who wants your stupid name?

440
00:35:49,063 --> 00:35:50,864
Do you know what my name means?

441
00:35:52,143 --> 00:35:52,663
No.

442
00:35:53,583 --> 00:35:56,944
Yuqiong means the sky,
so my nickname is Tiantian.

443
00:35:59,543 --> 00:36:01,784
With my name,
all the stars in the sky are yours.

444
00:36:03,784 --> 00:36:04,984
What is your nickname?

445
00:36:06,744 --> 00:36:07,583
It's Tiantian.

446
00:36:10,264 --> 00:36:13,143
You're really
scheming this one, Tiantian.

447
00:36:13,384 --> 00:36:15,663
You give me your name,
but you can still call it.

448
00:36:16,143 --> 00:36:17,223
You lose nothing.

449
00:36:17,223 --> 00:36:20,063
While I have to spend real money
to buy you a telescope.

450
00:36:21,304 --> 00:36:23,464
No, I can call myself that.

451
00:36:23,464 --> 00:36:25,864
If you buy the telescope,
you can use it too.

452
00:36:26,744 --> 00:36:27,824
No way.

453
00:36:29,143 --> 00:36:31,503
How about this? You give me your name.

454
00:36:31,984 --> 00:36:32,952
Don't go by He Yuqiong.

455
00:36:34,063 --> 00:36:34,936
Then what do I go by?

456
00:36:35,264 --> 00:36:36,304
Xiaoming.

457
00:36:37,503 --> 00:36:39,304
Anyway, I don't like that name.

458
00:36:39,824 --> 00:36:42,984
What? You're Xiaoming!
Give He Yuqiong back to me!

459
00:36:43,344 --> 00:36:46,824
He Yuqiong is mine.
I traded a telescope for it.

460
00:36:49,384 --> 00:36:50,103
Who's yours?

461
00:36:56,344 --> 00:36:57,623
You're sharper than me.

462
00:37:08,264 --> 00:37:10,744
Come back.

463
00:37:12,344 --> 00:37:12,844
Go.

464
00:37:17,703 --> 00:37:18,264
Get in.

465
00:37:33,744 --> 00:37:34,944
This year is still the same.

466
00:37:37,103 --> 00:37:38,304
I can forgive you.

467
00:37:39,103 --> 00:37:42,503
Like before. But if you did wrong,
you have to accept punishment.

468
00:37:55,304 --> 00:37:55,824
Don't move.

469
00:38:00,504 --> 00:38:05,061
(Qidaohezi, 2023)

470
00:38:22,552 --> 00:38:26,017
(Qingzhou)

471
00:38:29,384 --> 00:38:33,063
I said just grab a bite,
and you pick such an expensive place?

472
00:38:33,623 --> 00:38:35,223
Alright then, I'm paying for this meal.

473
00:38:35,623 --> 00:38:36,784
Are you joking with me?

474
00:38:36,784 --> 00:38:39,344
You visit me and you want to pay?
Who do you think I am?

475
00:38:39,703 --> 00:38:40,984
If I'm not paying, I won't eat.

476
00:38:40,984 --> 00:38:41,688
This way please.

477
00:38:42,304 --> 00:38:43,344
Fine, you pay.

478
00:38:44,464 --> 00:38:47,623
How'd it end up looking like
I dragged you here to mooch off you?

479
00:38:48,063 --> 00:38:51,744
I know this is normal for you.
You're here to show me the good life.

480
00:38:52,223 --> 00:38:53,103
Sit here.

481
00:38:54,703 --> 00:38:55,264
Thanks.

482
00:38:56,304 --> 00:38:57,103
Hello, who'll order?

483
00:38:57,543 --> 00:38:58,223
I'll do it.

484
00:38:58,223 --> 00:38:59,464
I'll do it.

485
00:39:00,223 --> 00:39:01,223
Fine, I'm paying anyway.

486
00:39:01,223 --> 00:39:03,304
Order what you like. I'll have the same.

487
00:39:03,744 --> 00:39:04,304
This one.

488
00:39:04,464 --> 00:39:05,703
The 1680 double set.

489
00:39:07,264 --> 00:39:08,344
Then bring it quickly.

490
00:39:11,103 --> 00:39:12,223
1680 sounds good.

491
00:39:13,864 --> 00:39:14,384
It's hot.

492
00:39:16,744 --> 00:39:19,503
Xiaoming, you look so good.
Different from when you were little.

493
00:39:20,824 --> 00:39:22,503
No wonder you've seen the world.

494
00:39:22,784 --> 00:39:23,384
This?

495
00:39:23,663 --> 00:39:24,464
Looks great.

496
00:39:24,464 --> 00:39:25,344
Don't I look old?

497
00:39:25,583 --> 00:39:26,944
No. Your hair looks wonderful.

498
00:39:27,183 --> 00:39:27,703
Really?

499
00:39:27,703 --> 00:39:29,183
I want those little curls too.

500
00:39:31,344 --> 00:39:33,424
Miss Ren, how about this bottle
of red wine?

501
00:39:34,143 --> 00:39:34,864
Is this wine okay?

502
00:39:35,744 --> 00:39:37,264
I'm on duty. I can't drink.

503
00:39:37,503 --> 00:39:38,264
Pour it for her.

504
00:39:38,543 --> 00:39:40,223
No. I'm driving, so I can't drink.

505
00:39:40,304 --> 00:39:41,304
Give it to her.

506
00:39:41,824 --> 00:39:44,543
What's up with this wine?
Is it part of the set meal?

507
00:39:44,703 --> 00:39:45,203
Yes.

508
00:39:46,304 --> 00:39:47,344
You take it.

509
00:39:47,583 --> 00:39:48,264
Let me see.

510
00:39:49,424 --> 00:39:51,223
Take it home and share it
with your husband.

511
00:39:51,344 --> 00:39:52,984
Why would I? We've got plenty of wine.

512
00:39:53,103 --> 00:39:54,223
You take it.

513
00:39:54,223 --> 00:39:54,744
No way.

514
00:39:54,764 --> 00:39:57,384
Wait. As a cop, I can't take this.
It'd be a violation.

515
00:39:57,384 --> 00:39:58,583
You take it.

516
00:39:59,183 --> 00:40:01,264
Alright then, I'll take it.

517
00:40:01,344 --> 00:40:03,063
Okay, I said you take it.

518
00:40:05,744 --> 00:40:10,464
Well then, cheers to our reunion
after all these years apart.

519
00:40:10,543 --> 00:40:11,964
Water instead of wine. Come on.

520
00:40:16,223 --> 00:40:17,703
Have this bread as a little starter.

521
00:40:17,824 --> 00:40:19,984
Alright, looks pretty good.

522
00:40:21,344 --> 00:40:22,503
Before coming to see you,

523
00:40:24,223 --> 00:40:25,424
I went to see Bai Shu.

524
00:40:26,503 --> 00:40:28,944
Bai Shu works
at the Rest Cemetery in Qidaohezi.

525
00:40:29,063 --> 00:40:29,944
I know.

526
00:40:30,984 --> 00:40:31,703
You know?

527
00:40:31,744 --> 00:40:32,344
Yes, I know.

528
00:40:32,623 --> 00:40:34,744
You were still in contact
with her back in 2009.

529
00:40:34,784 --> 00:40:36,264
How come you lost contact in 2010?

530
00:40:36,824 --> 00:40:39,784
I went to the U.S. in 2010.
How could I stay in touch?

531
00:40:40,703 --> 00:40:43,623
True, separated by the Pacific.

532
00:40:44,984 --> 00:40:48,503
Day here, night there. The time
difference makes it hard to connect.

533
00:40:50,023 --> 00:40:52,264
Bai Shu asked me
to pass on a message to you.

534
00:40:52,464 --> 00:40:55,784
She said you co-wrote
a diary together before.

535
00:40:55,784 --> 00:40:57,824
Said it's with you
and asked me to bring it back.

536
00:40:57,984 --> 00:40:59,864
What diary? I don't know
anything about that.

537
00:41:01,023 --> 00:41:04,424
That can't be right.
She told me very firmly.

538
00:41:04,784 --> 00:41:08,984
You two wrote a diary together,
and it's currently with you.

539
00:41:09,424 --> 00:41:11,784
There's no such diary. I have no idea.

540
00:41:15,984 --> 00:41:18,744
Look at you. You used to be so close.

541
00:41:18,984 --> 00:41:20,023
How did it come to this?

542
00:41:20,784 --> 00:41:22,264
I don't know what happened.

543
00:41:22,784 --> 00:41:25,864
Since I don't understand your situation,
I can't really judge.

544
00:41:25,984 --> 00:41:31,063
I just feel it would be such a shame
to end such a long friendship

545
00:41:32,103 --> 00:41:33,103
over this little benefit.

546
00:41:34,503 --> 00:41:35,944
Thanks for the reminder.

547
00:41:37,143 --> 00:41:38,984
Then take a message back to her for me.

548
00:41:39,543 --> 00:41:43,183
It's not like whatever she says goes.
This world runs on evidence.

549
00:41:43,984 --> 00:41:46,023
Even if she claims she has evidence,
I'm not afraid.

550
00:41:46,623 --> 00:41:48,143
I won't back down on this matter.

551
00:41:53,344 --> 00:41:55,824
Just tell her exactly what I said.

552
00:41:58,143 --> 00:41:59,503
Okay, message delivered for you.

553
00:41:59,984 --> 00:42:03,183
But I don't think classmates
need to become so hostile.

554
00:42:04,023 --> 00:42:04,824
Yes, right.

555
00:42:19,344 --> 00:42:20,223
I'm not finished.

556
00:42:20,864 --> 00:42:22,183
Please pack this up for her.

557
00:42:22,223 --> 00:42:22,744
Okay.

558
00:42:22,984 --> 00:42:24,663
I won't hold back then. I can eat this.

559
00:42:24,784 --> 00:42:25,384
Thanks.

560
00:42:28,384 --> 00:42:30,503
Is the pen you mentioned earlier

561
00:42:31,424 --> 00:42:33,464
related to the corpse-hiding case
at our school?

562
00:42:33,623 --> 00:42:36,703
Stop asking. This could easily
lead to a mistake.

563
00:42:38,663 --> 00:42:41,984
Fine, I won't ask. You police
really have it tough.

564
00:42:42,784 --> 00:42:45,784
The body was encased in concrete.
How could you find clues?

565
00:42:45,784 --> 00:42:47,224
It's finding a needle in a haystack.

566
00:42:48,063 --> 00:42:51,023
Yes. Even if it's a needle
in a haystack, we still have to find it.

567
00:42:51,264 --> 00:42:53,984
So, it would be great
if someone could provide clues.

568
00:42:54,384 --> 00:42:56,503
Actually, I wanted
to give you some clues.

569
00:42:57,183 --> 00:43:01,543
Ms. Zhou's pen was given
to both me and Bai Shu.

570
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
